cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving speech recognition using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses knowledge distillation, which is a technique used in machine learning to transfer knowledge from a large model to a smaller one, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves training and adaptation, which are topics covered in cs.SD (Sound). The use of neural networks also falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
